cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.PL

This paper deals with the application of Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS) algorithm to find better variable orderings for expression simplification. This topic falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as MCTS is a search algorithm commonly used in AI. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of a dynamic exploration-exploitation parameter, which is a common topic in machine learning and optimization, further supporting the categorization under cs.AI. The paper also involves the use of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) in the implementation of MCTS. The use of Simulated Annealing (SA) in combination with MCTS also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with the optimization of expressions, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL).
